29/03/2007
ATHENS, Greece -- The country's ombudsman, George Kaminis, presented a report Wednesday (March 28th) on complaints filed last year, saying most involved local self-government. 
The document, which was also submitted to Parliament, said of the 9,000 complaints he received, the majority concerned alleged mismanagement by municipal or prefecture administrators. 
The report also cited a high level of frustration with civil servants. 
(ERT - 28/03/07)
